That's the view of Hiroto Mitsugi, Assistant Director-General of the Food and Agriculture Organisation's Forestry Department, discussing how deforestation can be stopped worldwide, in line with the Sustainable Development Goal 15 target date, of 2020. 

He has been at United Nations (UN) Headquarters in New York this week to attend the 13th session of the UN Forum on Forests. 

The forum this week follows an international conference in February on how the world can go from "aspiration to action" concerning deforestation. He elaborates...

